(81, 1, '2012-05-25 17:57:54', '2012-05-25 17:57:54', '<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/151692_gaya-bikini_300_225.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-90" title="151692_gaya-bikini_300_225" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/151692_gaya-bikini_300_225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>Summer is just around the corner, so it’s time to blow the dust off the bikinis and tank tops. Whether it’s for a pool party, cookout, or just a plain walk in the sun, there’s no better feeling than having the perfect bikini body to show off. If you are interested in showing some skin come summertime, then keep reading for some great tips on how to get that bikini body you’ve always wanted.\r\n\r\nPeople gain weight over the winter simply because they don’t have to show off any skin. Plus the temperatures won’t allow it. And most of the times winter comes over the holidays, so you can’t help it if you go for second helpings. And if you really think about it, the summer and bikini season seems so far away, so why not overindulge a little.\r\n\r\nThese are just some of the things that go through people’s minds when summer isn’t upon them. At such times, people tend to exercise less and eat more. This is the reason for all that hanging meat (also called muffin tops) once the summer comes and what was hidden behind sweaters and parkas is revealed. At the time, it’s much easier to curl up on the couch and eat through that pizza than, say, get on a treadmill or jump rope. Even walking to the park would be great exercise at the time. Even though people know better, we still find ourselves lazing around, and then desperately rushing to get into shape once the sun shines.\r\n\r\nDespite all the cool adverts and belief, there is no overnight success crème or pill that will get you into that smoking bikini you saw at the shop. To get into shape requires hard work, dedication and commitment. The sooner you get started, the better.\r\n\r\nSeeing as we’ve tackled the reasoning behind all the weight gain during rest of the year, apart from summer, we may as well get on to how to get the bikini body. We can’t cry over spilt milk. We can, however, get on with trying to get in shape before the summer is upon us.\r\n\r\nThe first thing you have to do is watch your diet. In this regard, limit or completely eliminate all sugary, salty, and fatty foods from your diet. These kinds of foods not only contribute to weight gain; they also play a major role in heart and blood complications. In fact, if you eliminate them completely all year round, it would be great as it would enable you to live a healthier life. As an alternative, try including more whole grains, vegetables and fruits in your diet.\r\n\r\nA healthy diet will go a long way in ensuring that your body tones itself naturally. However, to help speed the process to the great bikini body, engage in regular physical exercise. Physical exercise can be as normal as walking a mile a day, or intensive like a 3 hour session at the gym. Remember, the target is to get that toned look, so do exercises that work the legs, arms and shoulders. Even taking the stairs is a great form of exercise, so don’t totally ignore them the next time you encounter stairs.\r\n\r\nExercise for some may be an ongoing process i.e. they do it every day, and thus are in great condition. This may not be the case with others who may need special attention to get a bikini body. If you belong to the latter group, then it would be advisable to get an exercise program that will target the body parts that will be exposed by a bikini. I’m talking about the arms, hips, buttocks, thighs and legs. All these muscle groups need different types of exercises, so find a trainer that can draft an exercise regimen to work these areas.\r\n\r\nBurning calories should not be left to the gym, there are a host of other activities that you can engage in and will give positive results. Plus, they can be done even during the winter, so you have no excuse not to stay in shape. Such activities would include skiing, trail hiking, swimming, sledding and tubing. Of course some of these activities will require special equipment, but if you really want to get and stay in shape, you will find a way to make them work. Plus, these activities are fun and may involve your family and friends.\r\n\r\nDuring spring time, the weather may permit longer walks and runs, and you can also add bike riding to the list of activities. And don’t forget the summer too, even though all the work and exercise has been geared towards this time of the year. The days are longer during summer, so involve even more activities. You can take up sports like volleyball and tennis which will work the arms and legs, while also burning the calories.\r\n\r\nGetting in bikini body shape will take more than just a few sessions at your gym; it will involve a whole lifestyle change. It may not be fun at the beginning, but you will see the results if you keep at it wholeheartedly. In due time, you will notice that your body is more trim, toned, and well shaped. This is the ideal scenario, and come summer time, you’ll be turning heads at the beach.\r\nNow that you have kept to the exercise schedule and made healthy living an everyday way of life, your body should reflect these changes. What’s now left is for you to put on some finishing touches on the project. I’m talking about some waxing or shaving of the legs and arms. Getting a tan should also be on the list.\r\n\r\nWhen all this is said and done, you should be able to walk down the beach and have jaws drop at the marvel that you have become. Yes, getting that bikini body might have required a lot from you, but at the end, you will be glad you did it.\r\n\r\nThe perfect bikini body doesn’t have to be reserved for magazine models and celebrities; get up now and get in shape before the summer rolls by!', 'With Summer Approaching, Get That Bikini Body', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'with-summer-approaching-get-that-bikini-body', '', '', '2012-05-25 18:25:50', '2012-05-25 18:25:50', '', 0, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/?p=81', 0, 'post', '', 0),
