(284, 1, '2012-09-05 21:00:29', '2012-09-05 21:00:29', '<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/napontadolapis1.jpg"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-286" title="napontadolapis" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/napontadolapis1.jpg" alt="" width="358" height="238" /></a>Time management is a key component for running any kind of business, and with fitness marketing, this can be a critical skill that makes all the difference between success and failure.\r\n\r\nThe many jobs required to run a fitness business successfully typically take up more time than is available, leading to a no-win bottleneck situation that only gets worse over time. Paying bills, training ground staff, getting fitness marketing packages and studio packages together, promotional activities and such essentials can bog you down over a period of time unless you’re wise with it.\r\n\r\nThis is where fitness guru Sam Bakhtiar’s Fitness Concepts boot camp can come in very handy, helping fitness business owners to utilize their time in a proper manner and setting them up for success that can be seen from the very first month after taking the course.\r\n\r\nBakhtiar tells his story, one that is mirrored over and over again with most fitness business owners trying to market, operate and manage their business – often single-handedly. “I started my fitness business flying by the seat of my pants. I was working 60 hours and finding it impossible to get everything done. I knew something had to give. That’s when I invested in more educational opportunities to find where I could improve my day-to-day business practices to free up more of my precious time.”\r\n\r\nThe results of his effort have manifested as the Fitness Concepts boot camp, which is offered nationally from his office in Chino, California. Bakhtiar is has a B.S. in Premed/Nutrition and a Doctorate in Chiropractic science, but he admits that all of his formal education did nothing to improve his expertise in fitness marketing. After attending many seminars and reading several books, he began to network his business. This is when a glaring fact became apparent: so far he had been completely off-track as far as marketing his fitness business went.\r\n\r\nToday, 20 years on, his company offers a business coaching and mentorship program that is available across the nation. “The program has been designed to put business owners on a fast-track to earning their first six or seven-figure salary,” Bakhtiar elaborates. “It starts with reading Six-Figures In 67 Days, a step-by-step manual that has helped people save $1,000 in business expenses in the first month and add on another $3,000 in monthly revenue right off the bat. This guide contains all of the industry’s best practices.” He adds: “Next, there is a retreat that assembles the industry’s biggest ballers to my Las Vegas mansion. It’s an extraordinary experience for business owners to surround themselves with fitness giants who are eager to talk with them in roundtable discussions that are much more intimate than your typical seminar or conference. It’s a great chance for people to ask their most burning questions and get answers from guys who have been there, done that.”\r\n\r\nBut Bakhtiar’s program is not merely about giving information and letting business owners plough through on their own. He says: “I never let anyone fall between the cracks. At the end of the day, how my fitness marketing program differs from others is the level of attention you get. I don’t just hand over the Six-Figures manual and say, ‘Well, good luck with that.’ I make sure you can put those steps into action and hold you accountable for success.”', 'New Fitness Marketing Program Discloses Importance of Time Management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-fitness-marketing-program-discloses-importance-of-time-management', '', '', '2012-09-05 21:00:29', '2012-09-05 21:00:29', '', 0, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/?p=284', 0, 'post', '', 0),
