(102, 1, '2012-06-25 19:01:14', '2012-06-25 19:01:14', '<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/helpinghand.jpg"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-104" title="helpinghand" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/helpinghand.jpg" alt="" width="245" height="366" /></a>You have made the commitment and time to get in the gym and get that slamming body that you’ve always wanted. This is all good news, and to top it all off, you have decided to enlist the help of a personal trainer. This is even better, as now your chances of getting in shape will be guided by a knowledgeable professional who will make the whole process safe, quick and as painless as possible.\r\n\r\nThis sounds too good to be true which it probably is because the odds of finding a great personal trainer are not entirely in your favor. So what makes a personal trainer a great one? If you truly are serious about getting back in shape, then there are factors that you should consider before hiring the next trainer you meet to be the one to get you going.\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Their accreditation</h2>\r\nThe first thing a great trainer has that sets them apart is they are correctly trained and registered. All great personal trainers have to be registered with an accreditation council for them to operate as trainers. The duration between registrations should be two years, to ensure that the personal trainer is up to date with the latest fitness education and training methods.\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Passion and desire</h2>\r\nThe next thing to look out for should be their passion and desire. A great personal trainer will be devoted to helping you improve your fitness level. They will be personally vested in your growth, while showing sincere desire to help you.\r\n\r\nThere are days when you will not feel like hitting the gym, or mornings when waking up early to hit the running trail will not feel like the best idea. It is during these times that great personal trainers will distinguish themselves, as they will motivate you to get up and go through those tough workouts.\r\n\r\nA great personal trainer should be more than just your fitness ‘supervisor’; you and the trainer should be a team working together to reach the seemingly impossible goals in fitness.\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Great communicator</h2>\r\nApart from any other qualities and attributes I mention here, a great personal trainer should also be great at communicating with others. This will help them get their message across more clearly, while also helping you understand what it is you must do in relation to your fitness regimen.\r\n\r\nIf a personal trainer is able to communicate with you in a great way, you will be more comfortable training, and this will show in your overall fitness results.\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Professionalism</h2>\r\nProfessionalism will range from the way they treat their clients, to other matters such as personal hygiene, dress code, and how they pay attention to clients while working them out. Some exercises might require some contact, so it goes that a personal trainer should know how and where to touch a client.\r\n\r\nProfessionalism will also extend to confidentiality guidelines, as a personal trainer is bound by the laws that guide any other health professional.\r\n\r\nProbably a last attribute is that a great personal trainer will come highly recommended. This is not always the case, but if they are doing their job well, it’s only natural that people will talk about them to their friends and families.\r\n\r\nMost of all, great personal trainers should be experts in their respective fields, and be able to transfer that knowledge and expertise to their clients.', 'What Makes a Great Personal Trainer?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-makes-a-great-personal-trainer', '', '', '2012-05-25 19:06:34', '2012-05-25 19:06:34', '', 0, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/?p=102', 0, 'post', '', 0),
