guish themselves, as they will motivate you to get up and go through those tough workouts.\n\nA great personal trainer should be more than just your fitness ‘supervisor’; you and the trainer should be a team working together to reach the seemingly impossible goals in fitness.\n<h2 dir="ltr">Great communicator</h2>\nApart from any other qualities and attributes I mention here, a great personal trainer should also be great at communicating with others. This will help them get their message across more clearly, while also helping you understand what it is you must do in relation to your fitness regimen.\n\nIf a personal trainer is able to communicate with you in a great way, you will be more comfortable training, and this will show in your overall fitness results.\n<h2 dir="ltr">Professionalism</h2>\nProfessionalism will range from the way they treat their clients, to other matters such as personal hygiene, dress code, and how they pay attention to clients while working them out. Some exercises might require some contact, so it goes that a personal trainer should know how and where to touch a client.\n\nProfessionalism will also extend to confidentiality guidelines, as a personal trainer is bound by the laws that guide any other health professional.\n\nProbably a last attribute is that a great personal trainer will come highly recommended. This is not always the case, but if they are doing their job well, it’s only natural that people will talk about them to their friends and families.\n\nMost of all, great personal trainers should be experts in their respective fields, and be able to transfer that knowledge and expertise to their clients.', 'What Makes a Great Personal Trainer?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '102-revision', '', '', '2012-05-25 19:06:16', '2012-05-25 19:06:16', '', 102, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/102-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
