(121, 1, '2012-05-25 17:46:12', '2012-05-25 17:46:12', '<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/slob.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-75" title="SONY DSC" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/slob.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="191" /></a>The subject of eating healthy and maintaining a balanced diet has been around for a long time. Eating healthy helps us to keep our bodies functioning well throughout the day and protects us against obesity and other diet related complications. It is therefore important for each and every one of us to know which foods to avoid, and which to keep. This information is not well known to all, thus many people have no idea that some of the foods they take may as well be contributing to their unending health complications.\r\n\r\nMaking a healthy choice will go a long way in improving the quality of your overall health, and life in general. Unhealthy foods will lead to weight gain, blocked heart arteries, blood pressure issues, among others. It is thus important that you know which specific foods to avoid, and stay away from completely.\r\n\r\nHere are some of the foods that you should stay away from and eliminate from your daily diet.The first types of foods to avoid are those that contain high levels of fat. In particular, saturated and hydrogenated fat. Most of these “fats” are found in butter, margarine, and shortening. The distinguishing feature of such kind of fat is that it tends to be solid at room temperature. Mono-saturated fat is the best kind of fat, and will be found in products such as olive and canola oil.\r\n\r\nTotally do away with sugar in your diet. I’m talking about table sugar and any kind of refined sugar. The latter is most used in snacks, candy, and other sweetened products. Sugar not only contributes to weight gain, it affects the blood sugar levels. The only kind of sugar in your diet should come naturally, such as that found in fruits.\r\n\r\nAt the other end of the spectrum is salt, and more specifically sodium. I only mention salt because it’s the most common source of sodium.  Too much sodium is bad for you as it negatively affects your blood pressure. That’s not to say that salt is bad; limiting your intake of salty foods should be the way to go. The most common culprits are canned foods, processed meats, and potato chips.\r\n\r\nThe fourth category of foods to avoid is those that have highly refined white flour as their main ingredient. The main culprits in this case are white bread, pasta, white rice, and such. This refined flour is also to be found in baked goods. They may be sweet to the taste and look delicious but they don’t add any nutrition to your body. In fact, they are just as fattening as sugar. Instead of highly refined white flour, try whole grain breads and cereals.\r\n\r\nGoing over the four categories looks like you’ll probably have an empty cupboard by the time you are done. If you read properly, however, you will notice that for every category of food to avoid, there is an alternative that is going to provide even better nutritional value.\r\n\r\nThe temptation to indulge at times may be great, and you probably won’t quit overnight, but eliminating the foods mentioned will help you live a longer and healthier life.', 'Foods to Avoid', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '74-revision-2', '', '', '2012-05-25 17:46:12', '2012-05-25 17:46:12', '', 74, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/74-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
