(133, 1, '2012-06-06 18:06:50', '2012-06-06 18:06:50', 'Fitness Website Gurus values our clients’ privacy and we want your online experience to be as hassle-free as possible. We realize that when associating with us, you are entrusting us with your sensitive personal information; as such, we go to great lengths to protect you and keep said information safe. The reason we collect as much data as possible is simple: we want to tailor our approach to meet your specific needs and to identify what differentiates you. See the statement below for a thorough disclosure of our privacy practices.\r\n\r\nCollected Information - There are several types of collected information. Fitness Website Gurus collects information directly from its users and from web server logs as well. User-supplied information is voluntarily supplied through request forms, and includes fields such as name, e-mail address, and phone number. The more information we have the better, because it allows us to build more effective SEO campaigns and enhance your experience with us.\r\n\r\nNext we have log information, which is provided when you visit a website. It usually includes, but is not limited to, Internet Protocol (IP) address, duration of visit, and referring location. Whenever you voluntarily disclose personal information online, it is information that can be collected and used by others. Fitness Website Gurus makes every reasonable effort to protect your personal information, however, Fitness Website Gurus cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us. You do so at your own risk.\r\n<h2>Cookies</h2>\r\nWe do use cookies (small files that are used to capture and remember certain information). If you enable them, cookies are transferred to your computer’s hard drive by sites/service providers through your browser. Cookies are essential to our services because they allow us to compile aggregate data regarding key site aspects such as traffic and interaction.\r\n\r\nYou can of course disable cookies through your browser’s settings, but be aware that some features of our site may not function properly. But remember, you may always place orders via telephone or email.\r\n<h2>Information Utilization</h2>\r\nWhenever you voluntarily provide personal information online, it is information that is out there and can be collected and used by others. Fitness Website Gurus makes every reasonable effort to protect your personal information, however, Fitness Website Gurus cannot ensure the security of any information you transmit to us. You do so at your own risk.\r\n<h2>Information Protection</h2>\r\nWe respect your privacy and view it as a priority. Under no circumstances will Fitness Website Gurus make your personal information available to third parties without your consent. Your access to some services and content may be password protected using secure encryption, therefore we recommend keeping your password confidential. Be aware of the phishing schemes that are out there, as Fitness Website Gurus will never send out unsolicited emails requesting your password.\r\n<h2>Data Security</h2>\r\nAll of your personal information is kept secure by Fitness Website Gurus. Only employees with proper clearance, agents and contractors (who have signed confidentiality agreements) have access to this information. We do not send out unsolicited emails, and regularly scheduled emails all contain the option to opt out or unsubscribe.\r\n<h2>Consent</h2>\r\nUsing our site implicitly means that you fully consent with our outlined privacy policy.\r\n<h2>Privacy Policy Changes</h2>\r\nWe reserve the right to modify our privacy policy. Policy changes will be posted on this page.', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'privacy-policy', '', '', '2012-06-21 22:55:37', '2012-06-21 22:55:37', '', 0, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/?page_id=133', 0, 'page', '', 0),
