(227, 1, '2012-07-30 21:31:35', '2012-07-30 21:31:35', '<strong>Who</strong>: IDEA Health and Fitness Association\r\n<strong>Where</strong>: San Diego, CA\r\n<strong>When</strong>: July 5th - 8th, 2012\r\n\r\n<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/2.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-201" title="2" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/2.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="240" /></a>A four-day fitness fest took over the wonderful city of San Diego from July 5th to the 8th. At the same convention center that plays host annually to Comic Con, more than 5,000 fitness professionals celebrated the industry that they love. We, the Fitness Website Gurus, were lucky enough to attend. The four-day festivities brought together thousands of professionals from seemingly everywhere to revel in the spirit of fitness and self-betterment. We all reflected on just how far the industry has come and also looked ahead, to the future. Making the event even more special was the fact that it was the 30th anniversary of IDEA. In celebration of this, the convention offered a number of unique activities and events. Some of the highlights included:\r\n\r\n• Actress (and fitness legend) Jane Fonda’s acceptance of the 2012 Jack LaLanne award for her countless contributions to the industry.\r\n• Keynote presentations by health expert Pamela Peek, MD, and The Biggest Loser’s Tara Costa.\r\n• A multitude of exhibits from companies at the forefront of the health food industry. All such exhibits included free samples.\r\n• Countless live training sessions led by respected fitness pros.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-202" title="1" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/1.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="240" /></a>Forward-thinking speakers held moving seminars on all sorts of topics, including personal training, group fitness, and nutrition. These seminars highlighted ground-breaking research, current trends, and advanced fitness programs across the globe. People came in droves just to hear some of these prominent individuals speak. It was really quite a spectacle to behold.\r\n\r\nIDEA’s co-founder and executive director Kathie Davis, had this to say prior to the start of the convention:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/3.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-205" title="3" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/3.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="240" /></a>"2012 IDEA World Convention is a launching point and defining moment for our industry. We believe the future of our industry is brighter than ever as fitness rapidly evolves into a more integrated, balanced circle of wholeness that merges body, mind and inspiration. Fitness professionals are at the forefront of this evolution, not just because they understand the fundamentals of fitness, but because of their authentic caring for the well-being of others, and their passionate belief in the power of every person to achieve their highest level of health and wellness. The education and product knowledge delivered at IDEA World is a fundamental part of the passion that drives our professionals."\r\n\r\n<a href="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/4.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-206" title="4" src="http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/4.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="240" /></a>Our own business is a testament to the progression of the wellness field and how technology has influenced it so profoundly. Nowadays you can schedule a training session with a few clicks, whereas before it was a long, often arduous process. Many visitors stopped by our booth and marveled at the basic concept that we were promoting – custom websites for personal trainers and fitness professionals. To us, the idea is only natural; if you’re going to be successful in the industry, then you had better establish a strong online presence. However, this came as a surprise to many, who had previously downplayed their web exploits. As you can imagine, a plethora of questions were fielded, as many of our services were foreign to booth attendees. People often approached us and said things like, “Wow, this is a very interesting niche,” or “You guys are really making websites for trainers?” To them we replied, “Someone’s gotta do it.”', 'The 2012 IDEA World Convention', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '198-revision-5', '', '', '2012-07-30 21:31:35', '2012-07-30 21:31:35', '', 198, 'http://fitnesswebsitegurus.com/198-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
